I think minimum of 122 Pottery is necessary<br>
<br>
{Unfired Velium Vial}<br>
Small brick of Velium<br>
3 Crystalline Silks<br>
2 Glass shards<br>
<br>
Combine in Pottery wheel<br>
<br>
{Velium Vial}<br>
Unfired Velium Vial<br>
HQ Firing sheet<br>
<br>
Combine in Kiln<br>
<br>
Find Frundle Frenlker in Thurgadin and ask her<br>
&quot;What Velium Vapors&quot;<br>
<br>
She will hand you a Velium Purifier<br>
<br>
Place the Velium Vial and 2 stackable pieces of Velium into the Purifier<br>
<br>
Click Combine and you have your Thurgadin Gate Potion<br>
<br>
NOTE<br>
The Velium Vial is not lore so you can have as many in stock as you wish along with a supply of stackable Velium Pieces<br>
<br>
